@startuml fig-udp-server-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam activityDiamondFontSize 11

title UDP server flow (recvfrom / sendto)

start

#E3F2FD:socket(AF_INET, SOCK_DGRAM);
#E3F2FD:bind((host, port));

note right
  No listen() or accept() —
  UDP is connectionless.
  Each datagram is independent.
end note

repeat
  #BBDEFB:data, addr = recvfrom(buffer_size);
  note right: blocks until a\ndatagram arrives
  #FFF9C4:process(data);
  #C8E6C9:sendto(response, addr);
repeat while (server running?)

#FFCDD2:close(socket);

stop

legend right
  1. Create a UDP socket and bind to host:port
  2. Enter the recvfrom loop (no connection state)
  3. Each datagram carries the sender address
  4. Reply with sendto using the sender address
  5. No teardown handshake needed
endlegend
@enduml
